  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Intimate partner violence (IPV) against women have negative mental health consequences for
      survivors; interventions designed to improve survivors' depressive symptoms and health status
      are limited.Present study evaluate the effectiveness of an integrated intervention in
      reducing intimate partner violence (IPV) improving health status.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
